Terraria's `Player`s handle double-taps in the cardinal directions (up, down, left and right) using the `player.doubleTapCardinalTimer[]` array

This array has 4 elements:
  [0] - double tap down
  [1] - double tap up
  [2] - double tap right
  [3] - double tap left

Double-taps also use these flags:
  `player.controlDown` and `player.releaseDown`
  `player.controlUp` and `player.releaseUp`
  `player.controlRight` and `player.releaseRight`
  `player.controlLeft` and `player.releaseLeft`

Here's what checking for a double-tap to the right for this game's player (`Main.LocalPlayer`) would look like:
```cs
//Do something if this game's player is double tapping to the right
//Note how we're using "controlRight", "releaseRight" and "doubleTapCardinalTimer[2]".
//  These all determine a double-tap to the RIGHT
int dirRight = 2;
bool playerPressingRight = Main.LocalPlayer.controlRight && Main.LocalPlayer.releaseRight;
if(playerPressingRight && Main.LocalPlayer.doubleTapCardinalTimer[dirRight] > 0){
    //The player has just double-tapped to the right.  Do something here
}
```

You'll need to store the old values of `doubleTapCardinalTimer` in PostUpdate and check against them in ResetEffects for the effect to be complete.

